                            <comment id="12611060" author="lchartier" created="Mon, 7 Jul 2008 11:10:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It seems that only code and reason are obtained from the original SOAPFault to create the new SOAP 1.2 SOAPFault.&lt;br/&gt;
It would be great to have the role and the detail to be translated too.&lt;br/&gt;
(&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/synapse/tags/1.1.1/modules/core/src/main/java/org/apache/synapse/core/axis2/SOAPUtils.java?revision=615753&amp;amp;view=markup&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/synapse/tags/1.1.1/modules/core/src/main/java/org/apache/synapse/core/axis2/SOAPUtils.java?revision=615753&amp;amp;view=markup&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12618957" author="saliya" created="Fri, 1 Aug 2008 08:17:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I tried to recreate your issue but was unsuccessful. I used a simple proxy service in Synapse with a SOAP 1.1. endpoint. Then I sent a SOAP 1.2 message to synapse which simply results in a SOAP fault (I intentionally sets a wrong EPR). I tracked the SOAP messages using TCPMon and the SOAP fault seems to get converted nicely. I even did a simple debug, yet it came out clean. See the SOAP faults given below.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SOAP 1.1 fault returned by the back end server.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;?xml version=&apos;1.0&apos; encoding=&apos;UTF-8&apos;?&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;soapenv:Envelope xmlns:soapenv=&quot;http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;soapenv:Body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
         &amp;lt;soapenv:Fault xmlns:axis2ns3=&quot;http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/soap/envelope/&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;faultcode&amp;gt;axis2ns3:Client&amp;lt;/faultcode&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;faultstring&amp;gt;The service cannot be found for the endpoint reference (EPR) &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8086/axis2/services/EechoService&amp;lt;/faultstring&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8086/axis2/services/EechoService&amp;amp;lt;/faultstring&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;detail /&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
         &amp;lt;/soapenv:Fault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;/soapenv:Body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;/soapenv:Envelope&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;SOAP 1.2 fault returned by Synapse after converting the previous one&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;lt;?xml version=&apos;1.0&apos; encoding=&apos;UTF-8&apos;?&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;soapenv:Envelope xmlns:soapenv=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2003/05/soap-envelope&quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;soapenv:Body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
         &amp;lt;soapenv:Fault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;soapenv:Code&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
               &amp;lt;soapenv:Value&amp;gt;axis2ns3:Client&amp;lt;/soapenv:Value&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/soapenv:Code&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;soapenv:Reason&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
               &amp;lt;soapenv:Text xml:lang=&quot;en&quot;&amp;gt;The service cannot be found for the endpoint reference (EPR) &lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:8086/axis2/services/EechoService&amp;lt;/soapenv:Text&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:8086/axis2/services/EechoService&amp;amp;lt;/soapenv:Text&lt;/a&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
            &amp;lt;/soapenv:Reason&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
         &amp;lt;/soapenv:Fault&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
      &amp;lt;/soapenv:Body&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
   &amp;lt;/soapenv:Envelope&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Saliya&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12751711" author="petabyte" created="Sat, 5 Sep 2009 06:01:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is the patch for SOAPUtils. Let me know your comments&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935682" author="werdex" created="Thu, 25 Nov 2010 08:15:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I had the same problem with soap conversion from 1.2 to 1.1 . Fault details is lost in SOAPUtils. Applying the patch solved the problem. Please include it in next release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12935759" author="ruwan" created="Thu, 25 Nov 2010 13:48:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks folks for the patch and the comments with verification of the patch, I will have a look and get this to the 2.0.0 release planned to be out next week.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Ruwan&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12966431" author="ruwan" created="Fri, 3 Dec 2010 05:55:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixed for the 2.0 release as well as on the trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
